definitions.definition: Of a subspecies : nominate , having a name which repeats the species name, designating that it represents the originally described population .

Of a subgenus or other infrageneric taxon : having a name which repeats the genus name, indicating that it includes the type species. For older botanical subgeneric and sectional names, it is sometimes prefixed with Eu- .
